laboratory_examinations.findings: White blood cell count of 15,100 per microliter (leukocytosis present).
Sinus tachycardia with evidence of left atrial and left ventricular (LV) enlargement.

LV ejection fraction of 40-45% with moderately decreased global LV systolic function; LV fractional shortening decreased at 18%; tricuspid valve had trace regurgitation; pulmonary artery systolic pressure normal with estimated right ventricular systolic pressure of 21 mmHg.
